The paper deals with streaming algorithms for data analysis, specifically clustering, shape fitting, rectangular matrix multiplication, and eigenvector verification. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.IT (information theory), and cs.LG (machine learning). Among these, cs.DS and cs.DM seem the most likely, as the paper focuses on algorithmic solutions for data analysis problems. However, the use of interactive proofs and communication complexity also suggests cs.CC and cs.IT as possible sub-categories. Finally, the mention of eigenvector verification and machine learning suggests cs.LG as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
